                    <!-- INTRODUCTION -->
                    <h4 id="list-item-1">Introduction</h4>
                    <p>
                        <strong>RSACPMS (Remote Sensing Application Project Management System)</strong> is a secure,
                        web-based platform designed to plan, manage, and monitor projects related to remote sensing
                        and geospatial applications. The system enables structured coordination among authorized users
                        while ensuring transparency, accountability, and efficient execution of projects.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        RSACPMS follows a role-based access model and supports project planning, progress tracking,
                        issue management, financial monitoring, meeting management, and automated reporting.
                        The platform is developed with a strong focus on data security, privacy, and compliance,
                        making it suitable for government and institutional use.
                    </p>

                    <!-- PROJECT SCOPE -->
                    <h4 id="list-item-2">Project Scope</h4>

                    <h5>Admin Role</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Register employees, assign roles, and send auto-generated login credentials via email.</li>
                        <li>Create projects and assign them to Project Managers or Subordinates.</li>
                        <li>Define project stages, timelines, and milestones.</li>
                        <li>View and manage all projects across the system.</li>
                        <li>Track project progress, budgets, and expenses.</li>
                        <li>View issues raised and actions taken by Project Managers.</li>
                        <li>Create meetings, manage attendance, add notes, and generate meeting reports.</li>
                        <li>Generate Employee, Project Activity, Meeting, and Expense reports in PDF and Excel formats.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Project Manager Role</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Login securely using assigned credentials.</li>
                        <li>Manage assigned projects and provide weekly progress updates.</li>
                        <li>Create new projects and assign subordinates.</li>
                        <li>Manage project stages, expenses, and timelines.</li>
                        <li>Schedule meetings and track attendance.</li>
                        <li>Create and manage unique Outsource entities and assign tasks.</li>
                        <li>Resolve project issues raised by subordinates.</li>
                        <li>Generate project and expense reports.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Subordinate Role</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>View assigned projects and responsibilities.</li>
                        <li>Raise project-specific issues and track resolution status.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Accounts Role</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Review expense requests submitted by Project Managers.</li>
                        <li>Approve, partially approve, or reject expense requests with proper justification.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Outsource Role</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Update and maintain the status of tasks assigned by Project Managers.</li>
                        <li>Ensure accountability and real-time task tracking.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <!-- USER MANUAL -->
                    <h4 id="list-item-3">User Manual</h4>
                    <h5>1. System Overview</h5>
                    <p>
                        RSACPMS is a role-based web application designed to manage, monitor, and control Remote Sensing Application projects.
                        The system supports project planning, execution, monitoring, financial control, issue management, meeting management, and reporting.
                    </p>

                    <h5>2. System Access Requirements</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Supported Browsers: Google Chrome, Microsoft Edge</li>
                        <li>Internet Connection: Required</li>
                        <li>Authorized Login Credentials: Provided by Admin</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>3. Login Procedure</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Open the RSACPMS portal.</li>
                        <li>Enter registered Username / Email ID.</li>
                        <li>Enter Password and click <strong>Login</strong>.</li>
                        <li>Logout: Click profile icon → Logout.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>4. Role-Wise User Manual</h5>

                    <h6>4.1 Admin</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Employee Registration:</strong> Add employees and assign roles. Login credentials are emailed automatically.</li>
                        <li><strong>Project Creation & Assignment:</strong> Create and assign projects.</li>
                        <li><strong>Project Stage Management:</strong> Define stages, timelines, and milestones.</li>
                        <li><strong>Minutes of Meeting:</strong> Create meetings, manage attendance, and add notes.</li>
                        <li><strong>Reports:</strong> Generate Employee, Project, Meeting, and Expense reports (PDF/Excel).</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h6>4.2 Project Manager</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Manage assigned projects and weekly updates.</li>
                        <li>Create new projects and assign subordinates.</li>
                        <li>Manage expenses, stages, and timelines.</li>
                        <li>Schedule meetings and track attendance.</li>
                        <li>Create and manage Outsources and assign tasks.</li>
                        <li>Resolve subordinate-raised issues.</li>
                        <li>Generate project and expense reports.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h6>4.3 Subordinate</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>View assigned projects.</li>
                        <li>Raise project-specific issues and track resolution.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h6>4.4 Accounts</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Review and approve/reject/partially approve expenses with remarks.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h6>4.5 Outsource</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Update task status assigned by Project Managers.</li>
                        <li>Maintain accountability and real-time tracking.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>5. Security Guidelines</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Do not share credentials.</li>
                        <li>Always logout after session.</li>
                        <li>Ensure data accuracy.</li>
                        <li>Report suspicious activity.</li>
                    </ul>

